		{
			"id": "about",
			"type": "page",
			"label": "About",
			"children": [
				{
					"id": "about_general_text",
					"type": "text",
					"text": "TAI - Assess Bias\n===============================\n\nThis custom step allows the user to evaluate predictive model bias across sensitive groups using the SAS procedure PROC ASSESSBIAS. The step takes a scored input table (containing a predicted probability column, (P_[ColumnName]) produced by a previous statistical/modeling step) and produces a series of tables that help the user understand fairness in their model:\n\nGroup Metrics — including number of observations, average squared error, and absolute error per sensitive group.\nMax Difference Between Sensitive Groups — depicting the \"worst case\" disparity across groups.\nBias Metrics — derived from the group metrics, capturing differences in average prediction, misclassification rate, and related measures.\n\nThe closer a bias metric value is to 0, the more similar the treatment was across sensitive groups.\n\nMore information about PROC ASSESSBIAS: https://go.documentation.sas.com/doc/en/pgmsascdc/default/casactml/casactml_assessbias_toc.htm",
					"visible": ""
				},
				{
					"id": "configuration_section",
					"type": "section",
					"label": "Configuration Tab",
					"open": true,
					"visible": "",
					"children": [
						{
							"id": "configuration_text",
							"type": "text",
							"text": "Input table — Select the scored table that contains the predicted probability column, the target variable, and the sensitive variable.\n\n\nPredicted Probability Variable — Select one or more probability columns (typically P_[TargetEvent]) generated by an upstream modeling step.\n\n\nSensitive Variable — Select exactly one column representing the sensitive grouping (e.g., a PII or demographic variable) on which bias will be assessed.\n\n\nTarget Variable — Select the actual target/outcome column.\nTarget Level — Choose Interval or Nominal.\nTarget Event (visible when Target Level = Nominal) — Select the event level of interest from the target variable.\n\n\nP Variables — Optional column used in the fitstat statement.\nP Event — Optional event for the FitStat probability variable, referenced from the target variable.\nDelimiter (visible when P Event is set) — Choose the delimiter used by the FitStat statement: Space ( ), Semicolon (;), Asterisk (*),  Period (.), or Comma (,)",
							"visible": ""
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"id": "options_section",
					"type": "section",
					"label": "Options Tab",
					"open": true,
					"visible": "",
					"children": [
						{
							"id": "options_text",
							"type": "text",
							"text": "Cutoff Ratio — Classification cutoff for predicted probabilities (range 0–1, default 0.5).\n\n\nNumber Of Bins — Number of bins used for binned bias metrics (min 2, default 20).\n\n\nNumber Of Cuts — Number of cutpoints used for cut-based bias metrics (range 2–100, default 100).\n\n\nSelection Depth — Selection depth percentage for depth-based metrics (range 1–100, default 10).\n\n\nFrequency — Optional frequency column.\n\n\nWeight — Optional observation weight column.",
							"visible": ""
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"id": "usage_section",
					"type": "section",
					"label": "Usage",
					"open": true,
					"visible": "",
					"children": [
						{
							"id": "usage_text",
							"type": "text",
							"text": "Required inputs: Input table, Predicted Probability Variable, Sensitive Variable, and Target Variable. If any of these are missing, the step will not execute PROC ASSESSBIAS; instead, an error messege saying \"PROC ASSESSBIAS will not run because one or more required variables are missing.\"",
							"visible": ""
						}
					]
				},
